  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Proyecto marco para las misiones de auditoria que se llevar&#xE1;n a cabo en Colombia en 2018

Se se realizar&#xE1;n las auditorias a los 5 clientes en Colombia en 2018 (COMSAB, FCC, COMEPCAFE,ECOLSIERRA y COMCACAOT)

The Agroindustrial Cooperative of Palmito Apropal, Agriterra&apos;s client since 2013, has achieved organic certification for a first group of partners representing an approx. of 170 H&#xE1;s those that produce an approximate of 11 containers per year out of a total of 40 conventional containers. It is expected to achieve a replication effect with more farmers who can achieve organic certification in a period no longer than 3 years. The expectation is that as they perceive the benefits of producing organic palm in terms of their individual income, as well as that of the Organization, this way of cultivating will spread throughout the Organization, taking care of the environment and strategically differentiating from the environment. competition.
This Project aims to strengthen the path already advanced in productive-organic, strategic and commercial issues, as well as to continue emphasizing work in governance that is still a weakness within the Organization.</narrative>
  </description>
